items.name: Emma Watson (SDXL 1.0 LoRA)
items.description:
It's one of my first attempts to train in SDXL. It's some kind of experiment, but I want to publish this one as results are quite cool in my opinion. There is of course enough space to improvements, but getting in consideration that images generated are only with SDXL 1.0 without refiner, I am happy by now with generations.

LoRA weights should be between 1.1 and 1.4 in my experience.

For portraits you can use 896 x 1152, 832 x 1216, 768 x 1344, 640 x 1536 or even 768x1024 resolutions.

This LoRA has been trained after carefully selecting 31 images. All photos have been enhanced to make the most of them. I hope you like it!

I don't ask for anything but any respectful constructive review (after having tested the model) would be highly appreciated or at least press Like if you're happy with results after trying it out! Thanks in advance and enjoy it!

Notice: This free work is intended for art and illustration purposes of emergent technology and not intended nor' trained for making illicit images, as the author I've taken care to not use any private data in the training process or designed it for such purposes. By downloading this model you are agreeing with the aforementioned intent and that you will not use my work to create / share images of a potentially immoral and / or illegal nature.

items.description:
Mysterious - SDXL Version

Please kindly rate my model with 5 stars and leave the images you've created with it. I would greatly appreciate that and it would bring me much happiness.

Alternatively, you can support me with a cup of coffee.

https://www.buymeacoffee.com/LahIntheFutureland

First of all, thank you for using my model. In terms of the concept, I wanted to create a fantasy atmosphere that leans more towards Asian culture, yet during the training process, I realized it still retains distinct elements of Western civilization. The efforts to update my model revolved around:

  • Enhancing image effects in a fantasy direction

  • Adding historical and cyberpunk imagery

  • Incorporating data on legendary creatures.

I expect this model to generate a world of imagination, either from ancient times or an urban future setting. And without a doubt, I will keep updating it to achieve these objectives!

U can try to add mysterious, fantasy

From V2.56 you can try anime/anime style/illustraion

Remember: High CFG Scale for Fantasy and Low (1-3) if u want realistic photos

Recommend:

Sampling Step: 30-60

Sampling Method: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras or Euler a

items.name: Kareena Kapoor - Textual Inversion
items.description:
This ti was requested by @wavorow56

Kareena Kapoor Khan is a prominent Indian actress and one of the leading figures in the Bollywood film industry. Kareena is the daughter of Randhir Kapoor and Babita Kapoor, and her elder sister, Karisma Kapoor, is also a well-known actress. Kareena Kapoor made her acting debut in the year 2000 with the film "Refugee." However, it was her role in "Kabhi Khushi Kabhie Gham" (2001) that catapulted her to stardom. Some of her notable films include "Jab We Met" (2007), "3 Idiots" (2009), "Bajrangi Bhaijaan" (2015), and "Udta Punjab" (2016), among others. Apart from her acting career, Kareena Kapoor is also admired for her fashion sense and has been a trendsetter in the Indian fashion industry.

Feel free to leave me a tip/buy me a coffee if you like what I am doing :) (I also do commissions)

items.name: Scamp (Kancolle)
items.description:
An experimental character LoRA of Scamp from Kantai Collection.

Info

Training with 78 images
Followed the manual form [ [Guide] Make your own Loras, easy and free ],
You can access to this guide in Suggested Resources section.

Recommended set up

Sampler: Euler a, DPM family series
Sampling steps: 20 or 25+
CFG Scale: 7
CLIP Skip: 2
*Do not use [restore face] on anime character!*

LoRA Weighting: [1 - 0.7]

Baking Step:
0. Drafting (512 x 512 res to find your desired sketch)
1. Hires fix (txt2img: 768 x 768, 768 x 512, 512 x 768, or above res)
2. inpaint (img2img: refine some unwanted effect, [Euler a] with 50+ step)
3. Upscaling (img2img: res*2 with [ControlNet Tile] & Ultimate SD upscale)

Upscaler for [Step 1 - 3]: [R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B, 4x-AnimeSharp, 4x-UltraSharp]
I always skip Step 0, 2 :P

Basic prompts

ScampKC, star (symbol), (star) hair ornament, (black) hair ribbon, (aqua) garrison cap, headgear, (black) one-piece swimsuit, (highleg) swimsuit, (competition) swimsuit, (white) gloves, (white) shorts, (short) shorts

Some additional tags that you may use for reference

-(left-side) elbow gloves
-candy, holding candy, lollipop
-tongue, tongue out
-machinery, rudder footwear, torpedo launcher, earphones
-brown eyes

items.name: Supermachine AbstractXL
items.description:
Hey everyone,

This is my first attempt at training a model on SDXL. It was trained on about 600 ghibli style images for 20 epochs. When testing, I found it produces quite nice abstract style images and excels at anime type images with a solid prompt.

We'll be training more models over the coming days and weeks as we get to grips with what works and what doesn't. These models will be available over at Supermachine.art where we offer the best that we create and open source with 50+ models available.

Anyone interested in the more spicy stuff can check out Nudes.AI for which we have added a bunch of textual inversion characters previously. I really like some of the outputs from this model compared to the base SDXL and it shows a ton of potential on a small dataset and limited epochs so that's super exciting!

PS. I am sorry this is a CKPT file and not Safetensors. Seems to be a bug with OneTrainer currently where the .safetensors output is causing an error, ckpt doesn't. If anyone can convert / know how to convert to safetensors, please get in touch and happy to add.

Thanks and enjoy!

items.name: Louise (Zero no Tsukaima)
items.description:
Hello Ulthy here. I created my first LoRA ever and decided to share. Trained on 81 images using AnythingV5Ink_v5PrtRE as training model.

I aimed to replicate anime version of this character.

As for generation I like AnythingV5Ink_v5PrtRE and Corneo's 7th Heaven Mix as base the most so far combined with kl-f8-anime2 vae.

Some settings I used for previews:

Euler a and DPM++ SDE Karras

Resolution 512x768, hires. fix, upscaler: RealESRGAN_x4plus_anime_6B, highres steps: 10, upscale x2, denoising strength: 0.4

sampling steps: 20

CFG scale: 6

Clip skip: 2

As for tags at the beginning use:

louise zero default, louise francoise le blanc de la valliere, 1girl, solo

Then for her default looks use:

pink eyes, pink hair, long hair, very long hair, wavy hair, hair between eyes, collared shirt, dress shirt, long sleeves, white shirt, black skirt, black miniskirt, pleated skirt, zettai ryouiki, black thighhighs, mary janes, black footwear, black cape, bolo tie, pentacle, pentagram

Negative tags I recommend:

holding, holding wand, wand, from back (if using cape)

This LoRA works decent with other checkpoints too tho I didn't test it that much, Hope you like. I might update this in near future.

items.name: bigger face for choosing
items.description:
This is a very simple pose dedicated to a specific purpose: selecting a face.

When testing different facial combinations, it can be challenging to choose the right face, especially as they might be facing different directions or showing various facial expressions.

This pose focuses only on the face, allowing you to judge without distractions.

It also works with very low-resolution images, enabling you to quickly experiment with many combinations of facial settings. These can be used later in your mass generation process.

V1.1 just moved the face downward a little so upper part of head could show.

This tool works better with dynamic prompt extension which can produce combinational or random choices.

My personal workflow is to generate a lot in a batch and cherry pick some preferred ones later.

items.name: Sigourney Weaver Lora
items.description:
Make sure to put "curly hair" to really get that 80s look for Sigourney. Take about big hair!

Be nice, have fun!

Susan Alexandra "Sigourney" Weaver (/sÉªËˆÉ¡É”Ërni/;[1] born October 8, 1949) is an American actress. A figure in science fiction and popular culture,[2] she has received various accolades, including a British Academy Film Award, two Golden Globe Awards, and a Grammy Award, in addition to nominations for three Academy Awards, four Primetime Emmy Awards, and a Tony Award.[3] In 2003, she was voted Number 20 in Channel 4's countdown of the 100 greatest movie stars of all time.[4]

Weaver rose to fame for starring as Ellen Ripley in Ridley Scott's science fiction film Alien (1979). She reprised her role in James Cameron's Aliens (1986), for which she received her first Academy Award nomination, and again in Alien 3 (1992) and Alien Resurrection (1997). The character is regarded as a significant female protagonist in cinema history.[5] She reunited with Cameron in Avatar (2009) and Avatar: The Way of Water (2022), two of the highest-grossing films of all time.[6] She also played Dana Barrett in the Ghostbusters films starting in 1984.

On Broadway, she received a Tony Award nomination for her role in the play Hurlyburly (1984). Further acclaim came for playing primatologist Dian Fossey in Gorillas in the Mist (1988), for which she won a Golden Globe Award, and in the same year, winning another Golden Globe Award for her performance in Working Girl. Weaver was the first actor to have two acting wins at the Golden Globes in the same year, and also received Academy Award nominations for both films. She won the BAFTA Award for Best Supporting Actress for her role in The Ice Storm (1997). Her other notable films include Copycat (1995), Galaxy Quest (1999), The Village (2004), Vantage Point (2008), Chappie (2015), and A Monster Calls (2016).

Weaver has also performed voice roles in the animated films The Tale of Despereaux (2008) and Pixar films WALL-E (2008) and Finding Dory (2016) as well as several documentaries, such as the BBC series Planet Earth (2006) and The Beatles: Eight Days a Week (2016). In television, she has received Primetime Emmy Award nominations for her starring roles in the movies Snow White: A Tale of Terror (1998), Prayers for Bobby (2009), and Political Animals (2013). She won the Grammy Award for Best Spoken Word Album for narrating the humour book Earth (The Book) (2010).

items.name: Diverse characters prompts
items.description:
Description

This wildcard is a modified version of the character.txt included in "Full Feature Character Prompts - Fantasy".

The objective is to offer more diverse combinations of characters, with various origins and more diverse women body shape (old, chubby, fit).

Usage

  1. In Automatic 1111, install the wildcard extension : https://github.com/adieyal/sd-dynamic-prompts

  2. Unzip the file in \stable-diffusion-webui\extensions\sd-dynamic-prompts\wildcards

  3. Use __character__ at the beginning of your prompt

Tips

  • Fully compatible with the prompts examples in "Full Feature Character Prompts - Fantasy"

  • Works well with locations from "Location Wilcards" for quick use

  • Tested on SDXL 1.0 with simple locations with success (example : " __character__ waterfront, boats docked, bustling harbor, seaside, digital painting, realistic, intricate, masterpiece, Sylvain Sarrailh")

  • Some models struggle to represent diversity, you may have to adjust scale or weights

  • The wildcard is in YAML format so everything can be in a single file. If you need to change the keyword, just change the first word of the YAML.

Credits

  • Most credits to TxcrTrl for Full Feature Character Prompts and his great LORAs

items.name: MedText-llama-2-70b-Guanaco-QLoRA-fp16 (Medical Knowledge LLM LoRA)
items.description:
This is a LoRA for the Llama-2-70b-Guanaco LLM. This is not a LoRA for Stable Diffusion.

This is a Medical Knowledge LoRA made for use with this model: llama-2-70b-Guanaco-QLoRA-fp16 https://huggingface.co/TheBloke/llama-2-70b-Guanaco-QLoRA-fp16) (you can use the quantized version of the model too).

I'm experimenting with making LLM LoRAs and thought this one tuned out good enough to share. Use at your own risk however, I am not a medical expert and do not take responsibility for the model producing incorrect information.

This LoRA was made using Oobabooga (https://github.com/oobabooga/text-generation-webui) and these training data: https://huggingface.co/datasets/BI55/MedText

I'll be working on various versions of this LoRA (and other types of LoRAs) as I explore the various ways in which to construct these add-on models.

The Hugging Face page for all this is here:
https://huggingface.co/AARon99/MedText-llama-2-70b-Guanaco-QLoRA-fp16

If you too are curious on how to construct these LLM based LoRAs, the Hugging Face page has additional information intended to help beginners, like myself.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. items.name: Anything / Kl-f8-anime2 / Vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned / Blessed / ClearVAE (fp16/cleaned)
items.description:
Anything / Kl-f8-anime2 / Vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned / Blessed / ClearVAE, but fp16/cleaned - smaller size, same result.

*my Telegram / Ko-fi / Hugging Face / Tensor.art - feel free to use files, contact or support me

Short version of the description:

The size of the usual versions of these VAE is 320+ megabytes, VAE from here is 160, the result of generation on both versions is identical/practically identical (more details below). Each VAE is available in .safetensors and .pt extensions.

About each VAE:

kl-f8-anime2: my favorite, original

+ good for anime/art, high saturation and contrast, your images will definitely be bright

- in models with initially high saturation, saturation may become excessive, may distort some details just because of the high contrast

anything: my plan b, original

+ good for anime/art, moderate saturation, no overburning of the image, good for models with high saturation

- in models with initially low saturation, the picture may turn out to be faded

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned: for kl-f8-like, but different details, original

+ good for realistic/semirealistic, a slightly different balance of saturation and contrast relative to kl-f8-anime, the same advantages (but not the same result)

- same issues as in kl-f8-anime2

blessed2 (fp16-version of this VAE uploaded by NoCrypt): never used it myself before, merge

+ contrast version of anything vae

- more artifacts than if you use anything vae

clearVAE V2.3 (fp16-version of this VAE by RedRayz): never used it myself before, merge

+ makes sense if the others didn't fit or for your checkpoint is reccomended this VAE

- pale picture, can give more artifacts than the previous ones

As with all parameters - there is no universal and ideal, each specific one will suit better in a specific situation. Often you have to try each one, and compare.

The more boring part of the description:

The ideal way to save maximum space on your SSD or HDD: using these VAE, you can always use the "no vae" version of checkpoints, and manually select VAE in the web-ui.

This gives:

a. saving space (checkpoints versions with VAE hang at least 2 gigabytes, "no vae" versions - 1.8~ = saving 160 megabytes from each model)

b. more control over the image style - the principle of VAE operation is largely similar to post-processing, so you can change "filters" in the form of VAE on the fly, and not be limited to one that is in the model itself (and most often it will be one of these VAE)

About the difference between regular VAE and fp16 VAE:

In many scenarios, there is no difference, but you can see minimal differences ("that house has a different window in the distance, a crease on clothes of a slightly different shadow tone", and so on) if you use certain hires.fix values. It happens when using hires.fix with "denoising strength" value above 0.3, I attached the last grid to demonstrate what differences between the usual VAE and fp16 VAE you can see (they're still not easy to spot right away) using high values - denoising strength: 0.5 / hires steps: 20.

About different VAE file names:

There are a huge number of VAE that are actually the same file that are constantly being renamed, so I chose 3 really different files (not considering Blessing2 / ClearVAE, because it's merges), and for me its enough of them for any image generation.

*my English is terrible, so feel free to point out mistakes in the text

The model is trained using a dedicated dataset, focusing on white stockings with lace tops. The first aim was to improve the rendering of white stockings for the Realistic Vision models, where stockings show often problems with lace top appearance.

IMPORTANT: The serie RealStockings is made by 3 different Loras:

https://civitai.com/models/111186/tanrealstockings-lace-top-sheer-stockings

All three Loras can be used together in the same image and make a sort of bundle, providing the same outfit for stockings of different colors.

WhiteRealStockings is based on SD 1.5, is optimized for Realistic Vision (checked also with 5.0) but also gives good results with other models, by changing the weight of the model or the weight of the trigger word.

WhiteRealStockings

visibile WhiteRealStockings top lace bands

items.name: Connie Nielsen
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Connie Nielsen is a Danish actress, mostly known for her roles as Lucilla in Gladiator (2000) and as Hippolyta in Wonder Woman (2017).

125-step TI trained on a dataset of 15 images with these settings.

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Do you have a specific idea for a TI in mind? Visit my website and let me know.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (c0nn1elsen:0.99), a woman as a movie star, modelshoot style, (extremely detailed CG unity 8k wallpaper), photo of the most beautiful artwork in the world, professional majestic oil painting by Ed Blinkey, Atey Ghailan, Studio Ghibli, by Jeremy Mann, Greg Manchess, Antonio Moro, trending on ArtStation, trending on CGSociety, Intricate, High Detail, Sharp focus, dramatic, photorealistic painting art by midjourney and greg rutkowski, (white turtleneck top:1.2), ((movie premiere)), (long skirt), ((standing near a movie theater)), ((paparazzi in the background)), (looking at viewer:1.2), (detailed pupils:1.3), ((closeup portrait:1.1))"

items.name: Huntress (Subverse) LoRA
items.description:
#1 Bounty hunter The Huntress from the game Subverse by Studio FOW. Works best on 0.9-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "HuntressSub, monster girl, colored skin, pink skin, tentacle hair" always needed, for consistency add "freckles, pink eyes".

Suggestions:

  • "HuntressOutfit" for her main outfit add "HuntressMask" for her Mask.

  • "pink eyes" help bring her eye color back if it fails.

  • Flexible with clothes but need to reduce weight to 0.8-0.9 to avoid the minor bleed from the main outfit. Reducing it any further can make normal hair mix with tentacle hair.

Who doesn't like a masked Alien gal like Tali from Mass effect? This LoRA turned out really well and the mask + outfit can be decently mixed and match with other outfits. Only a few Subverse characters remain but the last few have limited data so result quality with vary but I will see what I can do. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.
